The bug was caused by an out-of-bounds read when accessing pixel data in the image scaling process, likely due to improper handling of edge pixel contributions, which could lead to accessing memory outside the allocated bounds of the image array. This was addressed by adjusting the logic that calculates the contributions of edge pixels in the `_gdContributionsCalc` function.

